{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ketan/project/dropkick","sessionId":"3f1208fc-21f7-4873-bdce-4d7617029ebb","version":"2.1.72","gitBranch":"main","agentId":"a18f899e98a97220d","slug":"sleepy-munching-marble","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"You are implementing a CI system called \"Dropkick CI\". Create the following files in /home/ketan/project/dropkick/. Write ALL files completely - do not leave placeholders.\n\n## 1. `.gitignore`\n```\n*.retry\n__pycache__/\n.vagrant/\n```\n\n## 2. `CLAUDE.md`\n```markdown\n# Dropkick CI\n\nPolling-based CI system for WSL2 that monitors GitHub repos via SSH, runs test commands (including Dagger), and provides build history via Laminar CI's web UI.\n\n## Conventions\n\n- Bash scripts: always `set -euo pipefail`\n- Ansible: standard role layout, YAML with 2-space indent\n- `config/repos.yaml` is the single source of truth for monitored repos\n- All Laminar job scripts are auto-generated from repos.yaml — never edit them directly\n\n## Key Paths\n\n- `/etc/dropkick/repos.yaml` — deployed repos config\n- `/var/lib/dropkick/state/` — per-repo last-commit tracking\n- `/var/lib/laminar/cfg/jobs/` — auto-generated Laminar job scripts\n- `/var/log/dropkick/` — polling logs\n- `/run/dropkick/` — runtime (vault-pass, poll.lock)\n\n## Architecture\n\n- `dropkick` user: runs poll.sh, triggers jobs via laminarc\n- `laminar` user: runs laminard and job scripts\n- dropkick user is in laminar group for workspace access\n```\n\n## 3. `config/repos.yaml`\nAn example/template repos config:\n```yaml\npoll_interval_minutes: 5\n\nnotification:\n  email_to: \"ketan@example.com\"\n  email_from: \"ci@example.com\"\n\nrepos:\n  - name: example-project\n    url: \"git@github.com:user/example.git\"\n    branch: main\n    command: \"make test\"\n    # timeout: 1800          # optional, seconds\n    # notify_email: override # optional, overrides default\n```\n\n## 4. `ansible/ansible.cfg`\n```ini\n[defaults]\ninventory = inventory.yml\nroles_path = roles\nvault_password_file = /run/dropkick/vault-pass\nhost_key_checking = False\n```\n\n## 5. `ansible/inventory.yml`\n```yaml\nall:\n  hosts:\n    localhost:\n      ansible_connection: local\n      ansible_python_interpreter: /usr/bin/python3\n```\n\n## 6. `ansible/group_vars/all.yml`\nDefault variables used across roles:\n```yaml\n---\n# System\ndropkick_user: dropkick\ndropkick_home: /var/lib/dropkick\ndropkick_state_dir: /var/lib/dropkick/state\ndropkick_log_dir: /var/log/dropkick\ndropkick_run_dir: /run/dropkick\ndropkick_config_dir: /etc/dropkick\n\n# Laminar\nlaminar_version: \"1.3\"\nlaminar_home: /var/lib/laminar\nlaminar_cfg_dir: /var/lib/laminar/cfg\nlaminar_jobs_dir: /var/lib/laminar/cfg/jobs\nlaminar_bind_http: \"*:8080\"\nlaminar_bind_rpc: \"unix:/run/laminar/rpc.sock\"\nlaminar_title: \"Dropkick CI\"\nlaminar_keep_rundirs: 20\n\n# Polling\npoll_interval_minutes: \"{{ repos_config.poll_interval_minutes | default(5) }}\"\n\n# Notification\nnotify_email_to: \"{{ repos_config.notification.email_to }}\"\nnotify_email_from: \"{{ repos_config.notification.email_from }}\"\n```\n\n## 7. `ansible/playbook.yml`\nMain playbook that loads repos.yaml and applies all roles:\n```yaml\n---\n- name: Dropkick CI\n  hosts: localhost\n  become: true\n\n  pre_tasks:\n    - name: Load repos configuration\n      ansible.builtin.include_vars:\n        file: \"{{ playbook_dir }}/../config/repos.yaml\"\n        name: repos_config\n\n    - name: Set repos list fact\n      ansible.builtin.set_fact:\n        repos: \"{{ repos_config.repos }}\"\n\n  roles:\n    - base\n    - laminar\n    - msmtp\n    - ci-poller\n    - netbird\n```\n\nCreate all these files now. Make sure directories exist before writing.\n"},"uuid":"27ca7ffd-3e58-4a07-a042-0e4321d88afd","timestamp":"2026-03-11T05:11:36.490Z"}
